  {
    "client_msg_id": "1C76BA1F-BC59-4D06-8FD6-0A2B40D3CECE",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Not quite an answer…I haven’t read Tools for Conviviality, but I read Deschooling Society, and I think Illich is very much interested in something like “mutual aid.” Parts of that book are reminiscent of the dream of the early Internet, as he envisions using technology to match people based on shared intellectual interests to discuss ideas, all outside of any educational system. ",
